property.name: description
property.value: Test accessor that is similar to its base class, except that it requires the 'util' module. This tests both require() and this.extend().

property.name: untyped (port)
property.value: An untyped input that will accept any JavaScript object.

property.name: typeOfUntyped (port)
property.value: Produces the type (a string) of the input named 'untyped'.

property.name: jsonOfUntyped (port)
property.value: Produces a JSON representation of the input named 'untyped', created using the util module.

property.name: numericPlusP (port)
property.value: Produces the value of the 'numeric' input plus 'p'.

property.name: negation (port)
property.value: Produces the negation of the 'boolean' input.
